## 2. Database Schema

The database consists of the following core collections, utilizing references (`ObjectId`) for scalability.

### User Collection
- `_id`: ObjectId
- `name`: String
- `email`: String (Unique, Indexed)
- `password`: String (Hashed via bcrypt)
- `role`: Enum ['student', 'mentor', 'admin']
- `favoriteMentors`: [ObjectId(User)]
- `certificates`: [Object (CourseId, URL, IssueDate)]
- `timestamps`: true

### Course Collection
- `_id`: ObjectId
- `title`: String
- `description`: String
- `mentor`: ObjectId(User)
- `thumbnailUrl`: String (Cloudinary URL)
- `price`: Number
- `status`: Enum ['draft', 'published']
- `studentCount`: Number
- `averageRating`: Number
- `timestamps`: true

### Section Collection
- `_id`: ObjectId
- `course`: ObjectId(Course)
- `title`: String
- `order`: Number
- `timestamps`: true

### Lesson Collection
- `_id`: ObjectId
- `section`: ObjectId(Section)
- `title`: String
- `type`: Enum ['video', 'pdf', 'text']
- `videoUrl`: String (Cloudinary URL - if video)
- `pdfUrl`: String (Cloudinary URL - if notes)
- `content`: String (if text)
- `duration`: Number (in minutes)
- `order`: Number
- `timestamps`: true

### Assessment (Quiz/Assignment/Test) Collection
- `_id`: ObjectId
- `course`: ObjectId(Course)
- `section`: ObjectId(Section) (Optional - null if it's the Final Test)
- `title`: String
- `type`: Enum ['quiz', 'assignment', 'final_test']
- `content`: [Object (Question, Options, CorrectAnswer)]
- `passingScore`: Number
- `timestamps`: true

### Payment Collection
- `_id`: ObjectId
- `student`: ObjectId(User)
- `course`: ObjectId(Course)
- `amountPaid`: Number
- `platformFee`: Number (20% of amountPaid)
- `mentorEarnings`: Number (80% of amountPaid)
- `status`: Enum ['pending', 'completed', 'failed']
- `transactionId`: String
- `timestamps`: true

### Review Collection
- `_id`: ObjectId
- `student`: ObjectId(User)
- `course`: ObjectId(Course)
- `rating`: Number (1-5)
- `feedback`: String
- `timestamps`: true

## 3. Folder Structure

The application will feature a clear separation between frontend and backend within our monorepo/workspace.

### Backend Structure (MVC)
```text
backend/
├── config/           # Database connections, server configs settings
├── controllers/      # Route logic handlers (e.g., authController.js)
├── middlewares/      # authMiddleware (JWT verify, roles), fileUpload, errorHandlers
├── models/           # Mongoose schemas (User, Course, etc.)
├── routes/           # Express route definitions (authRoutes, courseRoutes, etc.)
├── utils/            # Helper functions (generateToken, cloudinaryUploader, validators)
├── .env              # Environment variables
├── server.js         # Main server entry point
└── package.json
```

### Frontend Structure
```text
frontend/
├── public/           # Static assets, 3D icons, manifest
├── src/
│   ├── assets/       # Images, styles, generic media
│   ├── components/   # Reusable UI components (Buttons, Modals, Navbar, CourseCard)
│   ├── context/      # State Management (AuthContext, CartContext, etc.)
│   ├── hooks/        # Custom React hooks (useAuth, useFetch)
│   ├── pages/        # Page components (Home, Login, Dashboard, CoursePlayer)
│   ├── services/     # Axios configurations and API calls (apiEndpoints.js)
│   ├── utils/        # Generic frontend helper tools
│   ├── App.jsx       # Main application layout and routes
│   ├── index.css     # Tailwind CSS base file (Light green & premium layout rules)
│   └── main.jsx      # React injection file
├── .env              # Client environment variables
├── tailwind.config.js# Tailwind specific branding theme
├── vite.config.js
└── package.json
```

## 4. API Route Structure

All API routes prefix: `/api/v1`

### Auth Routes (Public)
- `POST /auth/register` - Register a new user
- `POST /auth/login` - Authenticate user & return JWT token
- `GET /auth/profile` - Fetch logged-in user profile (Requires Auth)

### Users Routes (Admin / Student)
- `GET /users` - **Admin**: View all registered users
- `PUT /users/:id/ban` - **Admin**: Suspend/Ban user
- `DELETE /users/:id` - **Admin**: Delete user account
- `POST /users/favorites/:mentorId` - **Student**: Add/remove mentor from favorites

### Courses Routes
- `GET /courses` - **Public/Student**: Browse all published courses
- `GET /courses/:id` - **Public/Student**: View single course details
- `POST /courses` - **Mentor**: Create a new course
- `PUT /courses/:id` - **Mentor**: Update course details
- `DELETE /courses/:id` - **Admin/Mentor**: Delete a course

### Sections & Lessons Routes
- `POST /courses/:courseId/sections` - **Mentor**: Add a new module/section
- `POST /sections/:sectionId/lessons` - **Mentor**: Add lesson (Handles Cloudinary URL saves)
- `POST /sections/:sectionId/assessments` - **Mentor**: Add module quizzes/assignments

### Enrollment & Finances Routes
- `POST /payments/purchase` - **Student**: Purchase & enroll in a course
- `GET /payments/earnings` - **Mentor**: Fetch 80% earnings overview
- `GET /payments/revenue` - **Admin**: View 20% platform revenue & metrics
- `POST /courses/:id/complete` - **Student**: Mark complete & generate certificate

### Review Routes
- `POST /courses/:courseId/reviews` - **Student**: Drop a rating/feedback
- `GET /courses/:courseId/reviews` - **Public**: Read all reviews for a course

